      "comment": {
        "comments": [
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12665780/comment/13751669",
            "id": "13751669",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=stevel%40apache.org",
              "name": "stevel@apache.org",
              "key": "stevel@apache.org",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513"
              },
              "displayName": "Steve Loughran",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Europe/London"
            },
            "body": "This could be done in the AM by tracking when requests were made & acting when some haven't been satisfied after a given time period -which implies that the {{AMRMClientAsyncImpl}} could be extended to do this as it knows what is happening.\n\nHowever, that will make it stateful, on an AM restart the list of outstanding requests would be lost, and we can't use {{AMRMClient. getMatchingRequests()}} as you need to know the {{Resource}} capability you asked for.\n",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=stevel%40apache.org",
              "name": "stevel@apache.org",
              "key": "stevel@apache.org",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513"
              },
              "displayName": "Steve Loughran",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Europe/London"
            },
            "created": "2013-08-27T20:20:49.249+0000",
            "updated": "2013-08-27T20:20:49.249+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12665780/comment/14365080",
            "id": "14365080",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=stevel%40apache.org",
              "name": "stevel@apache.org",
              "key": "stevel@apache.org",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513"
              },
              "displayName": "Steve Loughran",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Europe/London"
            },
            "body": "This can actually be done in the client, which lets you do other policies such as decide when to relax placement, rather than rely on the cluster scheduler. ",
